   would benefit from understanding the spatial, demographic and
   attitudinal effects that play into consumption behavior, and such
   effects can be better understood when studying choice at the category
   and region level. Finally, public policies aimed at promoting healthier
   purchasing habits may have greater impact if special attention is given
