   services, we develop an analytic model of optimal pricing for hybrid
   bundles by a monopolist retailer. We derive and illustrate many useful
   propositions, several of which are counter-intuitive. Our results show
   that an increase in quality variability of the service is associated
   with a higher optimal hybrid bundle price and a lower optimal price of
