   method (participant type, study design, data source). Specifically, we
   reveal most differences for hedonic shopping environments and developed
   countries. Also, the store's advertising and atmosphere have gained
   importance in the Internet era, while purchase incentives, in-store
   orientation, and store location have lost relevance. This study
   contributes to a synoptic understanding of the comparable effectiveness
