   revenue sources typically are studied individually, rather than in a
   holistic fashion. In response, this study uses time-series data with 18
   million buyers and sellers from 2010 to 2011 and undertakes a
   quasi-experiment to analyze how the distinct effects of buyer-and
   seller-side strategies on revenues (1) vary across all three revenue
   sources and (2) depend differentially on a platform's upmarket
   repositioning strategy. The results show that buyers that purchase
   through direct traffic (e.g., typing in the site address) yield more
   display advertising and membership fee revenues than those gained
