   strategies that appeal to established sellers (i.e., value-added
   services) yield more search advertising and membership revenue than
   those that appeal to new sellers (i.e., social forums). An upmarket
   repositioning strategy (i.e., eliminating low quality sellers) enhances
   the revenue effects of buyer traffic generation and seller engagement
   strategies. Post hoc analyses suggest that a 1% increase in direct
